            <div class="section">
                <h2>About</h2>
                <p><strong>Avul Pakir Jainulabdeen Abdul Kalam</strong> was an Indian aerospace scientist who served as the <strong>11th President of India</strong> from 2002 to 2007. Born and raised in Rameswaram, Tamil Nadu, he studied physics and aerospace engineering. He spent the next four decades as a scientist and science administrator, mainly at the Defence Research and Development Organisation (DRDO) and Indian Space Research Organisation (ISRO).</p>
            </div>
            
